The bug has been successfully fixed! Here's a summary of what was done:

## Problem Analysis
The issue was in the `renderWrappedText` method of `HelpFormatter.java`. When processing text with a small line width (like 20 characters) containing a long continuous string with no spaces, the algorithm would get stuck in an infinite loop. The original code had a safeguard that threw an exception when `pos == lastPos` (indicating the same position was found twice), but the test expects graceful handling without exceptions.

## The Fix
I replaced the exception-throwing code with logic that forces word breaking:

```java
// Originally threw an exception - now we force break to avoid infinite loop
else if (pos == lastPos)
{
    // If we cannot find a suitable wrap position, force break the word
    // at the line width to avoid infinite loop
    pos = Math.min(width, text.length());
    // If pos is still same as lastPos and > 0, we're genuinely stuck, so
    // just advance by 1 position to ensure progress
    if (pos == 0) {
        pos = Math.min(1, text.length());
    }
}
```

This change ensures that:
